---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import Header from "../components/Header.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Terms">
  <Fragment slot="header">
    <Header />
  </Fragment>

  <section class="relative pt-32 pb-20 overflow-hidden bg-gradient-to-b from-ocean-50/80 via-surface-lighter to-white">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-dots-lg" />
    <div class="relative max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-10">
      <div class="max-w-3xl">
        <span class="section-label">Legal</span>
        <h1 class="text-5xl md:text-6xl font-heading font-bold text-stone-900 leading-tight mb-6">
          Terms &<br />
          <span class="gradient-text">conditions</span>
        </h1>
        <p class="text-sm text-stone-400">Last updated: 20 June 2026</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-16 md:py-20 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-10">
      <div class="prose-article space-y-8">
        <div>
          <h2>1. Introduction</h2>
          <p>
            These Terms & Conditions govern your use of the Protomon Labs website at <strong>protomonlabs.org</strong>. By accessing or using this website, you agree to be bound by these terms. If you do not agree, please do not use this website.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2>2. Intellectual Property</h2>
          <p>
            Unless otherwise stated, all content on this website — including text, graphics, logos, icons, images, audio clips, data compilations, and software — is the property of Protomon Labs or its content suppliers and is protected by applicable intellectual property laws.
          </p>
          <p>
            All source code for software tools developed by Protomon Labs and made available on this website is licensed under open-source licenses as indicated in the respective repositories.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2>3. Use of Content</h2>
          <p>
            You may view, download, and print pages from this website for your personal, non-commercial research or educational purposes, provided you do not:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Modify, republish, or redistribute the content without attribution</li>
            <li>Use the content for commercial purposes without prior written consent</li>
            <li>Remove any copyright or other proprietary notices</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            Scientific publications, preprints, and blog posts are made available for personal use. Proper attribution is required when citing our work.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2>4. Website Analytics and Tracking</h2>
          <p>
            This website uses privacy-preserving analytics to collect anonymised usage data. We use a self-hosted, cookie-free analytics service that does not track individual users across websites. No personal data is sold or shared with third parties.
          </p>
          <p>
            By using this website, you consent to the collection of anonymised analytics data as described in our Privacy Policy.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2>5. User-Generated Content</h2>
          <p>
            If you submit content through our contact form (including messages, questions, or suggestions), you grant Protomon Labs a non-exclusive, royalty-free license to use, reproduce, and adapt that content for the purpose of responding to your enquiry and improving our services. We do not publish user submissions without explicit consent.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2>6. Links to Third-Party Websites</h2>
          <p>
            This website may contain links to third-party websites (e.g., GitHub, Google Scholar, ORCID). We are not responsible for the content, privacy practices, or terms of those websites. Your use of third-party websites is at your own risk and subject to their respective terms.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2>7. Disclaimer</h2>
          <p>
            The content on this website is provided for informational purposes only and does not constitute professional advice. While we endeavour to keep the information accurate and up to date, we make no representations or warranties of any kind, express or implied, about the completeness, accuracy, reliability, or availability of the website or its content.
          </p>
          <p>
            Research findings, preprints, and blog posts represent the views of the authors and do not necessarily reflect the official policy of any affiliated institution.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2>8. Limitation of Liability</h2>
          <p>
            To the fullest extent permitted by applicable law, Protomon Labs shall not be liable for any direct, indirect, incidental, consequential, or punitive damages arising out of your access to, use of, or inability to use this website or its content.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2>9. GDPR Compliance</h2>
          <p>
            This website is designed to comply with the UK General Data Protection Regulation (UK GDPR) and the EU General Data Protection Regulation (EU GDPR). For information about how we handle your personal data, please see our <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a>.
          </p>
          <p>
            If you are located in the European Economic Area, you have the right to lodge a complaint with your local data protection supervisory authority.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2>10. Changes to These Terms</h2>
          <p>
            We reserve the right to update these Terms & Conditions at any time. Changes will be posted on this page with an updated "Last updated" date. Continued use of the website after changes constitutes acceptance of the new terms.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2>11. Governing Law</h2>
          <p>
            These Terms & Conditions are governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of England and Wales. Any disputes relating to these terms shall be subject to the exclusive jurisdiction of the courts of England and Wales.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2>12. Contact</h2>
          <p>
            If you have any questions about these Terms & Conditions, please contact us at:
          </p>
          <p class="text-stone-700">
            Email: hello@protomonlabs.org<br />
            Address: Protomon Labs, Computational Genomics Lab, Cambridge, UK
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <Fragment slot="footer">
    <Footer />
  </Fragment>
</BaseLayout>